This article is a letter from President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House, regarding the continuation of a national emergency with respect to export control regulations. The letter explains that according to the National Emergencies Act, a national emergency automatically terminates unless the President publishes a notice in the Federal Register and transmits it to Congress stating that the emergency is to continue. The President has sent such a notice, stating that the emergency caused by the lapse of the Export Administration Act of 1979 is to continue for one year beyond August 17, 2012.